This is my very first map!

I actually think its pretty good for a first try. I was planning on making a v2, but  first I wanted to hear what you guys think.

This is a very simple map: A dark maze, with some "secrets" inside. These are hidden within breakable walls. Even though there is no buy zones, and you only spawn with a deagle, you can find different weapons some places in the map. Just "Follow the light" ;)

The maze itself is not too compicated, but because of the lighting it is still a fun maze. it makes you feel like you are trapped inside. My original idea was making it all dark, so that you HAD to use your flashlight, but I figured it would be better only to have a few areas that way.

So, what do you guys think? I appreciate critiscism!

This is my remake of a map called "dead simple" from Doom3, the platforms lower to remove cover spots, and the map has teleporters.  The map currently only has 2 mp5's, 2 pump shottys, 1 auto shotty, 1 P90, 2 M249's, 1 M4A1, 1 scout, 1 AWP, and 1 AK47.  The map also has health packs, all weapon pickups glow and spin (just like in doom).  The platform in the middle rises to another platform where you can find the 2 sniper rifles.  Almost the whole map is visible from the platform. 

To get to the rising platform you have to be teleported, here is a tip: Don't be scared to fall.

EDIT: Thanks to Karatekäfer for the awesome skybox!

This map is my first full Counter-Strike: Source map. I'm mainly a single player Half-Life 2 mapper, but I decided to make a css map. I feel I was pretty successfully. My friends and I had a lot of fun playing it, and still do, and I hope you do too. Please excuse the bad texture alignment and low detail in some areas, I haven't mapped in a while. Concentrate more on the actual game play itself.

Features: 
Building that can be entered, and has a sniper spot. 
Thunder storm with randomized thunder and lightning.
Big layout.
Very fun with 20+ players/bots.
Dark night time atmosphere.
